headline: Goldman Sachs appoints 95 new partners: BBG
summary: Goldman Sachs (GS) is adding 95 executives to its partners list, initially reported by Bloomberg. This is the most additions seen under CEO David Solomon's leadership. The Morning Brief's Seana Smith and Brad Smith break down this announcement, noting 26 of the 95 new partners to be women. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Goldman names 95 new partners, most since 2010
summary: The bank touted the diversity of its new class, which included 26 women. But that’s 27%, short of 29% from two years ago. About 4% of new partners are Black, less than half the 9% from 2022.
